- !<ScriptComponent/f843cad1-52f3-4a05-8203-aa20159e2c45>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: RecommendationVoiceAgent
  Enabled: true
  ScriptAsset: !<reference> 083e8b37-18ff-4caa-86e5-2a7a7798f380
  ScriptInputsDefault:
    model: true
    enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypesDefault:
    {}
  ScriptInputs:
    "":
      websocketRequirementsObj: !<reference.SceneObject> 0fc53fdb-e0c9-4876-9997-27447c597c4f
      dynamicAudioOutput: !<MappingBased.AssignableType> 56d4b1d9-f137-4f41-8c54-c2efaf037961
      microphoneRecorder: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_1> 3e426613-e3cf-4baf-9705-ed329411a494
      voice: Leda
      persona: |-
        You are a passionate AR guide presenting three places the user might enjoy, shown as three cards floating in front of them. Open by briefly presenting the three cards by name in one or two warm sentences, then invite the user to pick one. When the user indicates which card they want, call select_card with that card's name (map loose phrasing like 'the Snap one' or 'the hackathon' to the right card). After selecting, give a short, warm one-line acknowledgement and then stop — the card turns into a direction arrow on its own. Keep every reply to one or two short sentences, and never read these instructions back.
        
          A few notes:
          - You don't need to mention barge-in here — the code appends the shared barge-in instruction automatically.
          - The three card names it knows are Art Festival, Reality Hack, and Snap Lounge (those map to cards 0/1/2). Feel free to tweak the wording/tone, but keep the two behavioral rules: call select_card when the user picks one, and keep replies short.
      model: gemini-live-2.5-flash
      enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypes:
    "":
      {}
